0 NECROMANCERS~
Since ancient times, scholars and priests have devoted their entire lives
to studying, explaining, and revering the final chapter in human life.
For some individuals, however, death has become an obsession, a source
of magical power, or even an object or religious adoration.
These beings are {Rnecromancers{x, and they are universally feared and loathed
as the purbeyors of unremitting evil.

Popular myth tells about {Rnecromancers{x practicing vile and forbidden arts.
He is the macabre sorcerer who roots about in graveyards, searching
out moldering components for his obscene spells.  She is the evil
priestess who calls upon restless, tormented spirits of the long
deceased, seeking their immortal arcana.  In their dark secluded
lairs, the mute undead, the monstrous familiar, and the ravening fiend
serve the necromancers in their ghoulish endeavors.

{RNecromancers{x begin with skills in {Gpolearm{x, {Gdagger{x and {Gscribe{x.  
